What you need to know:

Leicester sit atop the table after beating a lacklustre Chelsea 2-0 on Tuesday although both the Manchester clubs can go above them if they win their respective matches later on WednesdayRodgers, though, is wary of any such comparisons especially as his side faded in the run in to the title race last term and lost out on a Champions League spotRodgers is reportedly one of Chelsea's targets should Roman Abramovich fire Frank Lampard after a poor run of form